name: "Moon Face Moon" by Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)
description: [Colored pencil, brush pen, and paint pen on reclaimed cardboard with digital embellishments and color.] A collage of mental images, or (more precisely) a coagulation of muscular twitches and random ink distribution retouched to approximate creatures and faces. It means only that it exists. ---Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)
